Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and cook, stirring occasionally, until
golden, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Meanwhile, trim the @courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Lower the heat to medium, then add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} and courgette to the lardons.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until the veg is softened and starting to brown, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook lardons thoroughly.

Meanwhile, add the @linguine{180%g} to the pan of boiling water and bring back to the boil.
Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through
to stop it sticking together.

Add the @water{100%g} for the sauce, @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @mixed herbs{1%tsp}
to the bacon pan.

Stir and bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until slightly reduced,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Once reduced, stir in the @creme fraiche{150%ml} and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g},
adding a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Add the cooked pasta to the sauce. Toss to coat well and season to taste with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Serve your bacon linguine in #bowls{} sprinkled with the remaining cheese. Enjoy!